            "id": "dc38926c269f4cba98d2a",
            "questionText": "In a photoelectric experiment, a researcher illuminates a metal surface with light of frequency $!$f = 1.5 \\times 10^{15} \\text{ Hz}$!$. The stopping voltage required to completely suppress the photoelectric current is measured to be $!$V_s = 1.8 \\text{ V}$!$. Given that the charge of an electron is $!$e = 1.6 \\times 10^{-19} \\text{ C}$!$ and using Planck's constant $!$h = 6.626 \\times 10^{-34} \\text{ J s}$!$, determine the threshold frequency $!$f_0$!$ for the metal in Hertz $!$\\text{Hz}$!$.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "afe4644667bd4a479062a",
                    "stepText": "Let's begin by identifying the basic photoelectric equation that relates the kinetic energy of the emitted electrons to the incident photon energy and the work function of the metal. Please select the formula that best represents this relation.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "0a84b816-12f2-48c5-b801-70ddcbfa3381",
                        "b63cfff7-c0f2-44a2-84ab-5c9c9407941e",
                        "018e7d2e-cb2b-4daa-9c30-e3a0d9d369c9"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$eV_s = hf - hf_0$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$eV_s = hf_0 - hf$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$V_s = \\frac{hf - hf_0}{e}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "350aef49cc8441999bb55",
                    "stepText": "Great. Now, based on the selected equation, we know that the threshold frequency $!$f_0$!$ can be isolated from the equation. Please choose the correct rearrangement to solve for $!$f_0$!$.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "0a84b816-12f2-48c5-b801-70ddcbfa3381",
                        "4b705e18-0761-4dd4-a760-c05db44f5bba"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$f_0 = f - \\frac{eV_s}{h}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$f_0 = \\frac{eV_s}{h} - f$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$f_0 = f + \\frac{eV_s}{h}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "d566586892a34dfe95704",
                    "stepText": "Now that we have the correct rearrangement, let's compute the term $!$\\frac{eV_s}{h}$!$. Using the given values $!$e = 1.6 \\times 10^{-19}\\text{ C}$!$, $!$V_s = 1.8 \\text{ V}$!$, and $!$h = 6.626 \\times 10^{-34}\\text{ J s}$!$, calculate this quantity.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "4.35e14"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "Hz",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "fc61ca59-6b90-4172-8d29-30967a79b1ef",
                        "7f279d95-7489-4786-815c-960324474986"
                    ],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "6e6669372a35451aaef18",
                    "stepText": "Using the result from the previous step, substitute into the rearranged formula to find the threshold frequency $!$f_0$!$. Remember to subtract the computed value from the given frequency $!$f = 1.5 \\times 10^{15}\\text{ Hz}$!$.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
