            "questionText": "An electron with a kinetic energy of $!$250\\,\\text{eV}$!$ is used to study the crystal structure of a material using electron diffraction. Given that the mass of an electron is $!$9.11 \\times 10^{-31}~\\text{kg}$!$ and its charge is $!$1.602 \\times 10^{-19}~\\text{C}$!$, calculate the required accelerating voltage $!$V$!$ to achieve the given kinetic energy.",
